          "explanation": "рубль (rubl') = rouble. Russian currency unit."
        },
        {
          "prompt": "100 roubles: сто ___.",
          "type": "text-input",
          "answer": "рублей",
          "explanation": "100 → рублей (genitive plural). сто рублей."
        },
        {
          "prompt": "Do teens (11-19) follow the same zone rule as other numbers?",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "options": ["Yes — last digit determines the form", "No — teens always take genitive plural"],
          "answer": "No — teens always take genitive plural",
          "explanation": "Teens are the exception: all of 11-19 take genitive plural regardless of the final digit."
        }
      ]
    },
    "summary": {
      "rules": [
        "Teens (11–19): always take genitive plural — лет, рублей, etc. No exceptions.",
        "Tens: двадцать, тридцать, сорок (irregular), пятьдесят...восемьдесят, девяносто (irregular), сто",
        "Compound numbers: last digit determines the noun form (same counting zone rule as 1-10)",
        "сорок (40) and девяносто (90) are irregular — memorise them separately"
      ],
      "vocabulary": ["одиннадцать", "двадцать", "тридцать", "пятьдесят", "сто", "рубль"],
      "nextLesson": "Next: Unit 9 — Verb aspects. The perfective/imperfective distinction in full depth."
    }
